The paper deals with audio signal processing and source separation, which falls under the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SD). The paper also uses a neurally plausible sparse generative model, which suggests a connection to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with improving the quality of separated tracks, which could fall under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
